        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 1:45PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 145 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Waynesville, or near Smoky Mountains-Cataloochee,
moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Smoky Mountains-Cataloochee and Cove Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
